The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, April 07, 2004 				 Munda talks call to Buddha
																								Belda, April 6: Jharkhand chief minister Arjun Munda today held the Bengal government responsible for Naxalite violence and invited Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee to talks to tackle the menace.																								In this West Midnapore town to campaign for BJPs Midnapore candidate Rahul Sinha, Munda told reporters: I invite your chief minister to discuss with us how to deal with the extremists. 
